headline: 3 Consumer Stocks with Questionable Fundamentals
summary: The performance of consumer discretionary businesses is closely linked to economic cycles. Thankfully for the industry, all signs are pointing up as discretionary stocks have gained 13.9% over the past six months, beating the S&P 500’s 10.5% return.
